{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4815f63a-efda-4321-9a94-224e63beb9a1","content":"Here are **3 evaluation performance anti-patterns** in this project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. 🔴 File I/O Property Function (line 13, `EvalHeavy.csproj`)\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nProperty functions with file I/O execute **during evaluation** (before any targets run). This blocks the evaluation phase with disk reads. If the file were large or on a slow disk, this stalls every single build invocation — even no-op builds.\n\n**Fix:** Move this into a target with `Inputs/Outputs` so it only runs when needed, or use a `ReadLinesFromFile` task at build time.\n\n---\n\n### 2. 🟡 Expensive Recursive Glob (line 9)\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n`**\\*.*` walks the **entire directory tree** at evaluation time. If this repo grows (or sits alongside `node_modules`, `.git`, large asset folders), evaluation time balloons. The SDK already provides implicit globs for compilable items.\n\n**Fix:** Scope the glob to specific directories/extensions (e.g., `docs\\**\\*.md`) or add large directories to `DefaultItemExcludes` early.\n\n---\n\n### 3. 🟡 Deep Import Chain (3 levels)\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nEach import adds an evaluation pass. Here it's only 3 levels (minor), but this pattern tends to grow. In large repos, chains >20 levels deep measurably slow evaluation.\n\n**Recommendation:** Keep import depth shallow; flatten into a single shared `.props` when content is simple like this.\n\n---\n\n**Priority:** The `File::ReadAllText` property function is the most impactful issue — it forces synchronous I/O on every evaluation. The broad glob is next.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"44096f7a-c4f7-4f18-a6f1-0d7494211f98","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a clear picture of the project. Let me analyze it for evaluation performance issues using MSBuild evaluation knowledge.","outputTokens":529},"id":"65137533-e78e-4882-a652-4025dbdbe4f7","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:11:50.677Z","parentId":"c2c46f8f-895e-4cdd-9876-8ba915e403c8"}
